.TH "pdc_tx_list_sg_add" 9 "pdc_tx_list_sg_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdc_tx_list_sg_add \- Add the buffers in a scatterlist to the transmit descriptors for a given SPU. The scatterlist buffers contain the data for a SPU request message.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pdc_tx_list_sg_add
.BI "(struct pdc_state *pdcs "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdcs" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "sg" 12
Scatterlist whose buffers contain part of the SPU request
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If a scatterlist buffer is larger than PDC_DMA_BUF_MAX, multiple descriptors
are written for that buffer, each <= PDC_DMA_BUF_MAX byte in length.
.SH "RETURN"
PDC_SUCCESS if successful
< 0 otherwise
